## Section 12 — Windfall Acceleration Clause

### 12.1 — Baseline and Trigger

Any entity that has lifted the Human Rights Bar under Section 5.4, or that is
otherwise permitted to access and use this work ("Licensed Entity"), establishes
a Baseline Revenue at the time of their most recent payment to the author. A
Windfall Event occurs if, at any point during the twelve (12) months following
that payment, the Licensed Entity:

(a) Receives regulatory approval (FDA, EMA, PMDA, or equivalent) for a new drug,
    biologic, device, or indication that incorporates, derives from, benefits from,
    or was accelerated by the scientific content of this work;

(b) Announces a list price, wholesale acquisition cost, or average wholesale price
    for any drug treating the neonatal conditions described in narrative.md that
    exceeds one hundred ten percent (110%) of the price in effect at the time of
    their most recent payment;

(c) Closes an acquisition, merger, licensing deal, or asset purchase with a value
    exceeding USD $1,000,000,000 at any point during the paid period; or

(d) Reports quarterly or annual revenue attributable to products that incorporate,
    derive from, or were developed with access to the content of this work that
    exceeds one hundred ten percent (110%) of the Baseline Revenue for the same
    product line in the preceding comparable period.

Any single condition above, alone, constitutes a Windfall Event. No combination
is required.

### 12.2 — Supplemental Payment

Upon a Windfall Event, the Licensed Entity immediately owes a Supplemental
Windfall Payment equal to:

    Supplemental Payment = (Post-Trigger Revenue or Deal Value)
                           × 0.069
                           × (days remaining in license period ÷ 365)

For drug approval events (12.1(a)), "Post-Trigger Revenue" is the entity's
projected first-year revenue for the approved product, as stated in any investor
communication, analyst call, or regulatory submission made within 90 days of
approval. If no projection is made public, the floor is USD $1,000,000,000.

### 12.3 — Payment Deadline and Automatic Termination

The Supplemental Windfall Payment is due and payable within seven (7) calendar
days of the Windfall Event. No invoice or notice from the author is required.
The obligation is self-executing.

Failure to remit full payment within seven (7) days causes the license to
AUTOMATICALLY TERMINATE at 23:59:59 UTC on the seventh (7th) calendar day after
the Windfall Event ("Termination Moment"). No notice, cure period, or proceeding
is required. After the Termination Moment, any continued use constitutes willful
infringement subject to all remedies in Section 5.5, compounding from the date
of first use.

### 12.4 — Baseline Reset

Upon timely Supplemental Payment, the Baseline Revenue resets to the Licensed
Entity's then-current revenue figures for purposes of future Windfall Event
calculations within the same license period. Multiple successive Windfall Events
are possible and each resets the baseline.

### 12.5 — No Safe Harbor

Structuring product launches in tranches, delaying price announcements, spinning
off approved products into subsidiaries, or any comparable mechanism designed to
avoid or defer the Windfall Event trigger constitutes circumvention under Section
5.9 and the Termination Moment operates as if the Windfall Event occurred on the
date the triggering transaction was first substantially planned or disclosed
internally. Willful circumvention raises the restitution floor under Section 5.5
by 25% per detected instance.

